elop the foundations of the study of toric varieties, with examples, and describe some of these relations and applications. The text concludes with Stanley's theorem characterizing the numbers of simplicies in each dimension in a convex simplicial polytope. Although some general theorems are "ed without proof, the concrete interpretations via simplicial geometry should make the text accessible to beginners in algebraic geometry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aToric varieties. 7aMATHEMATICS / Geometry / Algebraic.2bisacsh  aAddition.  aAffine plane.  aAffine space.  aAffine variety.  aAlexander Grothendieck.  aAlexander duality.  aAlgebraic curve.  aAlgebraic group.  aAtiyah–Singer index theorem.  aAutomorphism.  aBetti number.  aBig O notation.  aCharacteristic class.  aChern class.  aChow group.  aCodimension.  aCohomology.  aCombinatorics.  aCommutative property.  aComplete intersection.  aConvex polytope.  aConvex set.  aCoprime integers.  aCotangent space.  aDedekind sum.  aDimension (vector space).  aDimension.  aDirect proof.  aDiscrete valuation ring.  aDiscrete valuation.  aDisjoint union.  aDivisor (algebraic geometry).  aDivisor.  aDual basis.  aDual space.  aEquation.  aEquivalence class.  aEquivariant K-theory.  aEuler characteristic.  aExact sequence.  aExplicit formula.  aFacet (geometry).  aFundamental group.  aGraded ring.  aGrassmannian.  aH-vector.  aHirzebruch surface.  aHodge theory.  aHomogeneous coordinates.  aHomomorphism.  aHypersurface.  aIntersection theory.  aInvertible matrix.  aInvertible sheaf.  aIsoperimetric inequality.  aLattice (group).  aLeray spectral sequence.  aLimit point.  aLine bundle.  aLine segment.  aLinear subspace.  aLocal ring.  aMathematical ind